<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Conversational Analytics on MCP Toolbox for Databases</title><link>https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/</link><description>Recent content in Conversational Analytics on MCP Toolbox for Databases</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>conversational-analytics-ask-data-agent</title><link>https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/conversational-analytics-ask-data-agent/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/conversational-analytics-ask-data-agent/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about">About&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>A &lt;code>conversational-analytics-ask-data-agent&lt;/code> tool allows you to ask questions about
your data in natural language.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This function takes a user&amp;rsquo;s question (which can include conversational history
for context) and references to a specific BigQuery Data Agent, and sends them to a
stateless conversational API.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The API uses a GenAI agent to understand the question, generate and execute SQL
queries and Python code, and formulate an answer. This function returns a
detailed, sequential log of this entire process, which includes any generated
SQL or Python code, the data retrieved, and the final text answer.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info</title><link>https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://googleapis.github.io/genai-toolbox/previews/PR-2517/resources/tools/conversational-analytics/conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="about">About&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>A &lt;code>conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info&lt;/code> tool allows you to retrieve
details about a specific data agent.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>It&amp;rsquo;s compatible with the following sources:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>conversational-analytics&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;code>conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info&lt;/code> accepts the following parameters:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>name&lt;/code>:&lt;/strong> The ID of the data agent to retrieve information for.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="example">Example&lt;/h2>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nt">tools&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">get_agent_info&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">kind&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">conversational-analytics-get-data-agent-info&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">source&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">my-conversational-analytics-source&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">description&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">|&lt;/span>&lt;span class="sd">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="sd"> Use this tool to get details about a specific data agent.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="reference">Reference&lt;/h2>
